ZH: 心脏通过主动脉将氧气富含的血液输送到全身。
EN: The heart pumps oxygen-rich blood to the rest of the body through the aorta.

ZH: 动脉疾病是导致心脏病和中风的主要原因之一。
EN: Arterial disease is one of the major causes of heart disease and stroke.

ZH: 动脉血栓是动脉的一种常见疾病。
EN: Arterial thrombosis is a common disease of the arteries.

ZH: 心脏手术常涉及修复或替换动脉。
EN: Heart surgery often involves repairing or replacing arteries.

ZH: 动脉供应着身体的组织和器官。
EN: Arteries supply tissues and organs throughout the body.

ZH: 健康的动脉是维护心血管健康的关键。
EN: Healthy arteries are key to maintaining cardiovascular health.

ZH: 动脉粥样硬化是一种常见的动脉疾病。
EN: Atherosclerosis is a common arterial disease.

ZH: 健康的生活方式可以降低患动脉硬化的风险。
EN: A healthy lifestyle can reduce the risk of developing atherosclerosis.

ZH: 健康的饮食有助于预防动脉堵塞。
EN: A healthy diet helps prevent artery blockages.

ZH: 动脉阻塞可能导致心脏病和中风。
EN: Artery blockages can lead to heart disease and stroke.

ZH: 动脉供血不足会导致缺血性中风。
EN: Inadequate blood supply to the arteries can cause ischemic strokes.

ZH: 高胆固醇水平可能导致动脉硬化。
EN: High cholesterol levels can lead to atherosclerosis.

ZH: 动脉炎是一种炎症性动脉疾病。
EN: Arteritis is an inflammatory arterial disease.

ZH: 动脉血栓会阻碍正常的血液流动。
EN: Arterial thrombosis can impede normal blood flow.

ZH: 动脉血管内膜受损可能导致出血。
EN: Damage to the arterial endothelium can lead to bleeding.

ZH: 动脉支承体是一种支持动脉的医疗器械。
EN: Arterial stents are medical devices that support arteries.

ZH: 动脉瘤是动脉壁的局部扩张。
EN: An arterial aneurysm is a localized dilation of an artery wall.

ZH: 轻微的动脉瘤通常不需要治疗。
EN: Mild arterial aneurysms often do not require treatment.

ZH: 动脉粥样硬化的早期症状往往不明显。
EN: Early symptoms of atherosclerosis are often subtle.

ZH: 心脏病患者需要定期检查动脉健康。
EN: Patients with heart disease need regular checks on their artery health.
